label: FICSHelpActivity
text: For more help visit • Players with (C) after the name are computer bots. • The chess clock does not start until both players have made their first move. Other There are separate ratings for Lightning Blitz and Standard. ��Ratings on FICS use the Glicko system.In the other systems the ratings changes for the two players in a game would balance each other out - if A wins 16 points B loses 16 points. That is not the case with this system. For more information vis Rating ��The "Resign" action resigns the game you are playing and gives your opponent the win. You will then be available for another gam Resign �eThe "Flag" action asks the chess server to check the clock time for you and your opponent. The Flag ��The "Draw" action offers your opponent a draw by agreement. The opponent can accept decline or just ignore the offer. If either the 50 move rule or 3 times repetition rule applies to the current position the draw command claims a dra Draw �2The "Abort" action is used to request aborting a Abort In-Game Actions The Watch game feature lets you view a game as it is being played updating the board as the players move. Watch game ��The Join game button will display only those current game ads for which you are eligible based on rating etc. To respond to a game ad select the game quickly or someone else will beat you to i Join game ��With the Create game button you can create a match offer for a player you know by name or issue a general offer that anyone can reply to given they have a rating in the requested interv Create game � Quick game Features A game is "Standard" if the expected duration of the game is 15 minutes or more per player. Standard A game is "Blitz" if the expected duration of the game is between 3 and 15 minutes per player. Blitz A game is "Lightning" if the expected duration of the game is less than 3 minutes per player. Lightning Game Types Play against thousands of chess players from all over the world! Help
